<\/ul><\/li>\n<li><p>Less commonly: the variation of a variable between the same season of different (often consecutive) years. Though this would more often be termed \"<strong>between years<\/strong>\". This is as opposed to \"between seasons\" which would be be between two different seasons of the same year.<\/p><\/li>\n<\/ol>\n","answer_id":43502,"question_id":43501,"up_vote_count":2,"last_edit_date":1455941529}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/43501/what-is-the-meaning-of-within-season-variation","last_activity_date":1455941529,"creation_date":1455926355,"answer_count":1,"title":"What is the meaning of \"within-season variation\"?","body":"<p>I am reading a paper about phenology and climate change for my assignment and I found this concept \"within-season variation\", can someone explain it to me? and how it is related to changes over time?<\/p>\n","question_id":43501,"tags":["climate-change","phenology"],"score":4,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":23,"up_vote_count":4},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/543344fdbc9b5b44bf53002e0dae9f15?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":6342,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6342/metacolin","reputation":118,"display_name":"metaColin"},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3f4b8c27dfec19d514f6f1ca42b29de4?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":6530,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6530/gwynfryn","reputation":66,"display_name":"gwynfryn"},"score":5,"is_accepted":true,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/543344fdbc9b5b44bf53002e0dae9f15?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":6342,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6342/metacolin","reputation":118,"display_name":"metaColin"},"score":0,"post_id":16983,"edited":false,"creation_date":1399781693,"comment_id":23571,"body":"Way cool. This is the best example I&#