y research regarding the biological function of this behavior? On a side note, I'm curious about how widespread this behavior is&mdash;is it only this species or is it nearly all land crabs?<\/p>\n","question_id":36554,"tags":["zoology","behaviour","invertebrates"],"score":11,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":304,"up_vote_count":11},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/cc9ec3d3dd4c8eb4ab42366701f5fcd3?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"unregistered","user_id":21976,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/21976/mohit-bansal","reputation":6,"display_name":"Mohit Bansal"},"closed_date":1455825498,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/43471/is-120-80-blood-pressure-at-lying-position-notmal-or-high","last_activity_date":1455824804,"creation_date":1455824804,"answer_count":0,"title":"Is 120/80 Blood Pressure at Lying position Notmal or high?","body":"<p>I was suffering from Anxiety and GAD for last 18 months. I used to have BP Shoot ups and it used to go till 170/105. Now I try to keep my mind Calm and I am trying to quit the medicine Xepar/Peroxetine. My BP now mostly is 120/80 while I am lying. I do not prefer measuring it sitting. At times after resting for 10-15 minutes and taking deep breaths it's around 115/75. Is it normal or High? As I can see that the recommended way of measuring BP is sitting and keeping the hand higher at the level of heart. <\/p>\n","question_id":43471,"tags":["cardiology","psychology"],"score":1,"down_vote_count":0,"closed_reason":"off-topic","is_answered":false,"view_count":27,"up_vote_count":1},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-on6yuwN5JEs/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAABU/8oD_p798mqw/photo.jpg?sz=128","user_type":"registered","user_id":16460,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/16460/sanjukta-ghosh","reputation":432,"display_name":"Sanjukta Ghosh","accept_rate":38},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1sIMq.jpg?s=128&g=1",