ough it's a bit hard to tell from the photo.<\/p>\n","answer_id":43435,"question_id":38850,"up_vote_count":4}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/38850/which-organism-is-this","last_activity_date":1455727884,"creation_date":1442494725,"answer_count":1,"title":"Which organism is this?","body":"<p>Place: Bangalore, India<\/p>\n\n<p>Month: September, 2015<\/p>\n\n<p>Current weather: Cloudy and rainy<\/p>\n\n<p>Google images search was just giving me dragonfly photos. That organism is on grass blade.<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/YTRav.jpg\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/YTRav.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>Image is captured by me.<\/p>\n","question_id":38850,"tags":["species-identification","identification"],"score":6,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":95,"up_vote_count":6},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://graph.facebook.com/1573387156211772/picture?type=large","user_type":"registered","user_id":21951,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/21951/swastik-mohapatra","reputation":1,"display_name":"Swastik Mohapatra"},"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/43434/how-to-use-the-10-20-system-of-placement-with-3-leads-in-eeg","last_activity_date":1455727702,"creation_date":1455727702,"answer_count":0,"title":"How to use the 10-20 system of placement with 3 leads in EEG?","body":"<p>I am trying to get EEG signals using a homemade circuit. I have 2 active electrodes and a reference electrode. My question is, can I implement the 10-20 system of electrode placement by connecting the electrodes of the lobes together? Or, do I need separate electrodes for each position? \nThe project is for interfacing the brainwaves to a computer so not much accuracy is needed. <\/p>\n","question_id":43434,"tags":["brain","electroencephalography"],"score":0,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":15,"up_vote_count":0},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/v8wX2.png?