ised to learn that the vas deferens detours over the pubic bone instead of taking the obviously more direct path.<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://human.biodigital.com/widget?be=u1P&amp;uaid=1ly5V\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://human.biodigital.com/widget?be=u1P&amp;uaid=1ly5V<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>Because I would assume that the vas deferens is more prone to damage facing the front. Also its damage would put procreation at stake.<\/p>\n\n<p>Hence my question: Is there a biological reason for this path? Some advantage which outweighs or balances its disadvantages?<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/OSTWG.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/OSTWG.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/a><\/p>\n","question_id":43433,"tags":["human-biology","evolution"],"score":0,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":64,"up_vote_count":0},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/29Cvo.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":6088,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6088/yusaf-khaliq","reputation":108,"display_name":"Yusaf Khaliq"},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/v5upF.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3624,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3624/fileunderwater","reputation":10502,"display_name":"fileunderwater"},"score":3,"is_accepted":true,"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1395246050,"creation_date":1395224813,"body":"<p>You are basically correct. Most common usage in my experience:<\/p>\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inbreeding\" rel=\"nofollow\">Inbreeding<\/a><\/strong> refers to sexual reproduction between genetically closely related individuals, within a species. Inbreeding will increase the relatedness between individuals in a population.<\/p>\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interbreeding\" rel=\"nofollow\">Interbreeding<\/a><\/strong> refers to reproduction with another species (or race), and is often used as a synonym to <em>crossbreeding<\/em> or <em>hybridization<\/em> (when referring to hybrid offspring from two different species/races/breeds, not DNA hybridization). This is also how '<em>Interbreeding<\/em>' is defined in the <a href=\"http://www.oed.com/view/Entry/97546?redirectedFrom=interbreed#eid\" rel=\"nofollow\">Oxford English Dictionary<\/a>. However, '<em>Interbreeding<\/em>' is sometimes used just to signify that two individuals can breed and have viable offspring (\"<em>...these two individuals can interbreed...<\/em>\"), and under this usage this can also include/overlap with inbreeding.<\/p>\n\n<p>The latter usage can be seen in the <em>Species<\/em> article in <a href=\"http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/558649/species?anchor=ref76052\" rel=\"nofollow\">Encyclopædia Britannica, online<\/a>:<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p><strong>Species<\/strong>, in biology, classification comprising related organisms that share common characteristics and are capable of interbreeding.<br>\n  ...<br>\n  Interbreeding only within the species is of great importance for evolution in that individuals of one species share a common gene pool that members of other species do not.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n","answer_id":15941,"question_id":15940,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1395246050},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/13341e960b9d9b7072c8bae38036c62e?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"unregistered","user_id":21949,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/21949/ghulam-azhar","reputation":1,"display_name":"ghulam azhar"},"score":-2,"is_accepted":false,"down_vote_count":2,"last_activity_date":1455722988,"creation_date":1455722988,"body":"<p>interbreeding is a process in which same kind of species are breed together such as(male and female)but outer breeding is a process in which different kind of species are breed together such as(means horse is a specie it will breed with bitch those are different species <\/p>\n","answer_id":43432,"question_id":15940,"up_vote_count":0}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/15940/difference-between-inbreeding-and-interbreeding","last_activity_date":1455723537,"creation_date":1395221917,"answer_count":2,"title":"Difference between inbreeding and interbreeding","body":"<p>Is inbreeding the same as interbreeding?<\/p>\n\n<p>On this site <em>interbreeding<\/em> is defined as (<a href=\"http://www.thefreedictionary.com/interbreeding\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.thefreedictionary.com/interbreeding<\/a>):<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <ol>\n  <li>To breed with another kind or species; hybridize.<\/li>\n  <li>To breed within a narrow range or with closely related types or individuals; inbreed.<\/li>\n  <\/ol>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>But I am sure that interbreeding is not the same as inbreeding. Inbreeding would be between genetically related members of a species and interbreeding would be between genetically un-related members of the same or different species.<\/p>\n\n<p>after looking at wikepedia pages for both terms as well as searching the english oxford dictionar I am certain they are different<\/p>\n","question_id":15940,"tags":["terminology","reproductive-biology","sexual-reproduction"],"score":1,"accepted_answer_id":15941,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":2605,"up_vote_count":1,"last_edit_date":1455723537},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/pVoco.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":14587,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/14587/the-nightman","reputation":1330,"display_name":"The Nightman","accept_rate":50},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8338f9b96b1c61599df745d61145b0c2?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":15878,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15878/243","reputation":959,"display_name":"243"},"score":0,"post_id":36252,"edited":false,"creation_date":1437438960,"comment_id":59991,"body":"Do you want to amplif